---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Oliver Richman — the maker behind Oliver Tate Furniture. Bespoke furniture inspired by curves in nature, built in Cleveland, Ohio."
>

  <section class="about-hero section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label">The designer-maker</span>
      <h1 class="section-heading">About</h1>
      <div class="divider"></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-body section">
    <div class="container about-layout">

      <!-- Photo -->
      <div class="about-photo-wrap">
        <img src="/images/profile_photo.jpg" alt="Oliver Richman, maker" class="about-photo" />
        <p class="photo-caption">Oliver Richman</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Bio -->
      <div class="about-text">
        <h2>Oliver Richman</h2>
        <p>
          Oliver is a furniture designer & maker based in Cleveland, Ohio. Under the name
          <em>Oliver Tate Furniture</em>, he designs and builds custom pieces
          for clients who want something made specifically for them — furniture that makes you reach out and touch it, 
          and then makes you want to talk about why.
        </p>
        <p>
          His work is driven by a exploring how nature and the human form can be captured
          within a piece of functional, artistic furniture. He draws inspiration from his environment, including
          the curve of a leaf, the hamstring tendons of a ballerina, and the shadows of mountains. 
          Oliver believes contributing to aesthetic diversity in the built environment is an integral part of human expression.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every commission begins with a conversation about how you live, what
          the piece needs to do, and what draws you to certain shapes, forms, or styles. The design
          follows from that — drawn by hand, refined in the shop, built once
          and built right.
        </p>

        <div class="divider"></div>

        <h2>The process</h2>
        <ol class="process-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Discovery.</strong>
            <span>We talk — ideally in person or over a video call —
            about what you need and what you're drawn to. I ask a lot of questions.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Design.</strong>
            <span>I produce hand sketches and, for complex pieces,
            a scale drawing. We refine until the form feels right, then I send a
            written proposal with a fixed price and estimated timeline.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Build.</strong>
            <span>I select the wood personally — grain, figure,
            and character matter as much as species. I send photos as the piece
            takes shape in the shop.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Delivery.</strong>
            <span>I personally deliver when locale allows around the Great Lakes region, and ship globally with our trusted logistics partners. 
            White-glove handling, every time.</span>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: var(--space-8);">
          Start a conversation
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.about-hero { padding-block-end: var(--space-8); }
.about-body  { padding-block-start: 0; }

.about-layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  gap: var(--space-12);
  align-items: start;
}

@media (min-width: 900px) {
  .about-layout { grid-template-columns: 300px 1fr; }
}

/* Photo */
.about-photo-wrap {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--space-3);
  position: sticky;
  top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-8));
}

/* On mobile (single-column), sticky makes the photo overlap the text — disable it */
@media (max-width: 899px) {
  .about-photo-wrap {
    position: static;
  }
}

.about-photo {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  object-fit: cover;
  border: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
}

.about-photo-placeholder {
  overflow: hidden;
  background: var(--color-surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-dark);
}

.about-photo-placeholder svg {
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
}

.photo-caption {
  font-size: var(--text-xs);
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  font-style: italic;
  text-align: center;
  max-width: none;
  margin: 0;
}

/* Text */
.about-text h2 {
  font-size: var(--text-2xl);
  margin-block-end: var(--space-4);
}

.about-text p {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  margin-block-end: var(--space-5);
}

.process-list {
  list-style: none;
  counter-reset: process;
  /* Shared 3-column grid: [counter] [label] [description] */
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: auto max-content 1fr;
  column-gap: var(--space-4);
  row-gap: var(--space-5);
  padding: 0;
  margin-block-end: 0;
}

.process-list li {
  /* "Dissolve" the li so its children become direct grid items */
  display: contents;
  counter-increment: process;
}

.process-list li::before {
  content: counter(process, decimal-leading-zero);
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: var(--text-2xl);
  color: var(--color-wood);
  opacity: 0.5;
  line-height: 1;
  align-self: baseline;
}

.process-list li strong {
  align-self: baseline;
}

.process-list li span {
  color: var(--color-text-muted);
  align-self: baseline;
}
</style>
